(177, 1, '2023-08-08 12:20:13', '2023-08-08 12:20:13', '<em>‘Children are like buds in a garden and should be carefully and lovingly nurtured, as they are the future of the nation and the citizens of tomorrow,\' said India\'s first prime minister’- Jawaharlal Nehru </em>\n\nEducation is an essential component in a child\'s life as it enhances their skill, personality and attitude. It plays a pivotal role in a child’s life. Education acts as the wind beneath the wings for children to grow as healthy and successful adults in the future. Most importantly it acts as a tool that decides whether the individual was content or happy as an adult or turns out as a depressed one. Pre-primary education in India is provided to children between 3 to 6 years by kindergarten. ‘Kindergarten’ is actually a German word which means <em>children’s garden</em>. These schools have varying names for different levels of classes, beginning from – Pre-Nursery, Nursery, KG, LKG (Lower Kindergarten), and UKG (Upper Kindergarten). However Nowadays, most people start school as early as possible, and there are many private school options available in cities. So, choosing a best kindergarten can feel like a daunting task.  So how do you choose a best kindergarten for your little one?\n\nWhen it comes time to find the perfect kindergarten for your little one, it is important to keep several things in mind:\n\n<strong>Find a school that matches your child’s temperament: </strong>Understand your child’s learning style when narrowing down your top choices. Some schools will have very specific teaching styles, while others will have a broader approach to learning.<strong>\n</strong>\n\n<strong>Location and travel time:</strong> It is preferable to send your little one to a school that is located near your home.  Safety is of course one of the first things that comes to mind. But if the school is far away, or inconvenient, you need to determine if the benefit outweighs the trouble.\n\n<strong>Affiliation:</strong> Do proper research and homework about their affiliation.\n\n<strong>Faculty:</strong>  The biggest influences on your child will be the teachers they interact with. So, you have to know whether the faculties are enthusiastic, inspired or passionate or not.\n\n<strong>Curriculum:</strong> Remember public kindergartens follow a standardized curriculum and private kindergartens follow a customized one. So do proper research before stepping away. Search for a balanced curriculum including fees etc.\n\n<strong>Class-size:</strong> Always be attentive to class size. Remember in small classes, teachers are able to attend to each student every day, many times a day. Make sure the child-to-teacher ratio is sufficient for optimal learning.\n\n<strong>Talk to current parent:</strong> Parents usually have relevant information. Ask them why did they choose the school? What is the expectation for parent involvement? You will get a lot of ideas about the school environment and every small thing regarding issues.\n\n<strong>Visit:</strong> You are the best judge of what is right for your child, so trust your instincts and visit the school before admission.\n\n<strong>Learning should be fun:</strong> When you visit the school, notice that are the kids’ faces those of happy, involved children? If a child feels the joy of learning, everything else comes naturally.\n\n<strong>Speak with the principal before you leave: </strong>Ask the principal as many questions as you can. This is the person that should have all the answers. A principal’s philosophy will teach you a lot about a specific school and the way they view education.\n\nAlways remember that quality education aims to ensure the development of a fully-rounded human being. Choosing the best kindergarten environment for your child requires careful consideration. Remember, you will only make this decision once, so don’t take chances and choose wisely.    	', 'Here\'s how to choose the best kindergarten for your little one', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'heres-how-to-choose-the-best-kindergarten-for-your-little-one', '', '', '2023-08-08 12:20:13', '2023-08-08 12:20:13', '', 0, 'http://localhost/bolograhak/blog/?p=177', 23, 'post', '', 0),
(179, 1, '2023-08-08 12:28:30', '2023-08-08 12:28:30', 'In recent years online shopping has gained immense popularity, leading to the rise of various e-commerce platforms. With just a few taps on our smartphones we can have our needy thing delivered right to our doorstep. However, beneath the convenience lies a hidden world of additional charges that customers often overlook. This type of deceptive pricing practices undermines consumer trust and harm the reputation of e-commerce platforms. By implementing transparent pricing strategies and adhering to consumer protection regulations, platforms can foster a trustworthy and reliable environment for online shopping. Consumers, on the other hand, must remain vigilant and report any misleading practices. In this post, we will shed light on how various platforms add different fees such as platform fees, surge fees, packing fees, handling fees and more often discreetly and without customers\' awareness.\n<ol>\n 	<li><strong> Platform Fees: </strong>Many delivery platforms charge a certain percentage as a platform fee to merchants for utilizing their services. While this fee may be reasonable it often gets indirectly passed on to customers through higher prices or additional charges. Be aware that this fee is typically not prominently displayed during the ordering process.</li>\n</ol>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n 	<li><strong> Surge Fees: </strong>During peak hours or high-demand periods, delivery platforms may impose surge fees to manage increased orders effectively. While this practice can help balance supply and demand customers may be caught off guard when they realize the substantial increase in their billings. It is essential to check for any surge-related charges before placing your order especially during busy times.</li>\n</ol>\n<ol start=\"3\">\n 	<li><strong> Packing and Handling Fees: </strong>Some delivery platforms add packing and handling fees to the total bill which is usually meant to cover extra expenses associated with packaging materials and handling logistics. These charges might seem insignificant, but they can add up quickly especially for multiple orders or larger groups. Always review the detailed breakdown of charges to ensure transparency.</li>\n</ol>\n<ol start=\"4\">\n 	<li><strong> Promotional Pricing vs. Final Billing: </strong>Many platforms entice customers with promotional pricing such as discounts free delivery or buy-one-get-one offers. However, make sure to check the final billing before confirming your order. Some platforms may revert to the regular higher prices without explicitly mentioning this during the ordering process. Pay close attention to any discrepancies between the advertised price and the final bill.</li>\n</ol>\nSellers are becoming increasingly creative when it comes to squeezing a few more bucks out of you on the sly. To lure customers, sellers advertise only the base price. Then, at the time of payment, a host of charges are tacked on as mandatory fees and the customer usually discovers this too late. Even to attract customers, various platforms often implement promotional strategies and use enticing tactics including displaying lower prices during the browsing phase. However, an alarming trend has emerged where some platforms showcase discounted prices to lure customers but charge the full price during the final billing process. This type of deceptive practice not only erodes trust but also raises serious concerns regarding consumer rights. Ultimately, the onus is on the consumers themselves. Take the time to carefully go through the terms and conditions document, no matter how bulky it is. Even always ask for a printed confirmation of the final rate quoted, so that you have proof to fight a legal battle if any mishaps happen. By staying informed and attentive, we can make more informed decisions and ensure that we are getting the best value for our money. However, ask for a written or printed or digital  confirmation of the final rate quoted, so that you have proof to fight a legal battle.    	', 'Be aware of Hidden Charges: It\'s important to value your money', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'be-aware-of-hidden-charges-its-important-to-value-your-money', '', '', '2023-08-08 12:28:30', '2023-08-08 12:28:30', '', 0, 'http://localhost/bolograhak/blog/?p=179', 21, 'post', '', 0),
