(314, 1, '2023-08-16 09:20:03', '2023-08-16 09:20:03', 'Customer reviews are mainly opinions that customers write about a company\'s products and services for others to read. Many people read these reviews to learn more about businesses and research their products or services before making a purchase. And customers are 63% more likely to trust brands with online reviews compared to brands with no reviews. Actually, it has created a new field in online marketing and communication that bridges the gap between traditional word-of-mouth and a viral form of feedback.\r\n\r\nHere are five important reasons why online customer reviews are important.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong> Provide social proof:</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Online reviews provide social proof to potential customers. They probably won’t believe everything you have to say about the product or service. However, personal recommendations and word-of-mouth are much more powerful.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: left;\" start=\"2\">\r\n 	<li><strong>online reviews validate expertise:</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Most consumers trust online reviews by their peers more than the claims made by a company. Consumers are less likely to believe a claim if there isn’t any third-party supporting evidence. Good reviews are a great way to back up your claims.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: left;\" start=\"3\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Influence purchasing decisions:</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Online reviews directly influence the buying decisions of your target market. According to one study, having as few as five reviews makes products 270% more likely to sell compared to products with no reviews.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: left;\" start=\"4\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Reviews Generate More Reviews:</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The appearance of several reviews seems to be opinion enough to give new customers the incentive and confidence to submit their own on a particular product or service. So, it encourages other visitors to leave their own feedback.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: left;\" start=\"5\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Better understands your customers and improve Customer Service:</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Customer reviews can tell you things you may not know, including human factors such as staff behaviour. Not everyone complains when they are dissatisfied. But all the reviews left by your customers, helps your company understands overall customer satisfaction and customer service.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"></p>', 'Five top reasons why customer reviews are important', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'five-top-reasons-why-customer-reviews-are-important', '', '', '2023-08-16 09:20:03', '2023-08-16 09:20:03', '', 0, 'http://localhost/bolograhak/blog/?p=314', 1, 'post', '', 0),
(315, 1, '2023-08-07 12:30:10', '2023-08-07 12:30:10', 'Customer reviews are mainly opinions that customers write about a company\'s products and services for others to read. Many people read these reviews to learn more about businesses and research their products or services before making a purchase. And customers are 63% more likely to trust brands with online reviews compared to brands with no reviews. Actually, it has created a new field in online marketing and communication that bridges the gap between traditional word-of-mouth and a viral form of feedback.\n\nHere are five important reasons why online customer reviews are important.\n\n<img class=\"wp-image-148 alignright\" src=\"http://localhost/bolograhak/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/review-576x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"270\" height=\"480\" />\n<ol>\n 	<li><strong> Provide social proof: </strong>Online reviews provide social proof to potential customers. They probably won’t believe everything you have to say about the product or service. However, personal recommendations and word-of-mouth are much more powerful.</li>\n</ol>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n 	<li><strong>Online reviews validate expertise: </strong>Most consumers trust online reviews by their peers more than the claims made by a company. Consumers are less likely to believe a claim if there isn’t any third-party supporting evidence. Good reviews are a great way to back up your claims.</li>\n</ol>\n<ol start=\"3\">\n 	<li><strong> Influence purchasing decisions: </strong>Online reviews directly influence the buying decisions of your target market. According to one study, having as few as five reviews makes products 270% more likely to sell compared to products with no reviews.</li>\n</ol>\n<ol start=\"4\">\n 	<li><strong> Reviews Generate More Reviews: </strong>The appearance of several reviews seems to be opinion enough to give new customers the incentive and confidence to submit their own on a particular product or service. So, it encourages other visitors to leave their own feedback.</li>\n</ol>\n<ol start=\"5\">\n 	<li><strong> Better understands your Customers and improve Customer Service: </strong>Customer reviews are a gateway to customer experience. Reviews are the only trustworthy way to know if customers are liking a product and are enjoying using it. Thus customer reviews are a crucial factor for businesses to judge their performance. Once the customer reviews are analyzed, the shortcomings of current strategies can be improved to ensure better customer service.</li>\n</ol>\nCustomer reviews can tell you things you may not know, including human factors such as staff behavior. Not everyone complains when they are dissatisfied. But all the reviews left by your customers, helps your company understands overall customer satisfaction and customer service.    	', 'Five Reasons Why Customer Reviews are Important', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'five-reasons-why-customer-reviews-are-important', '', '', '2023-08-07 12:30:10', '2023-08-07 12:30:10', '', 0, 'http://localhost/bolograhak/blog/?p=147', 28, 'post', '', 0),
(316, 1, '2023-08-10 11:25:10', '2023-08-10 11:25:10', 'The <span style=\"color: #000000;\">E-Daakhil </span>is an online portal that allows grahak to file complaints at their convenience from anywhere, diminishing the requirement of their physical presence at consumer commissions. It also allows consumer commissions to scrutinize these online submitted complaints and accept, reject or forward these to the concerned commission for further processing. This online portal launched on 7th September 2020 by The National Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission (NCDRC).\nHere are the steps to follow for lodging an online complaint in different forums:\n\n1. Go to the portal E-Daakhil (<a href=\"https://edaakhil.nic.in/edaakhil/\"><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\">https://edaakhil.nic.in/edaakhil/</span></a>)\n\n2. Click on the \"Complain\" button located at the top left corner of the page.\n\n3.Then register by providing personal information including name, phone number, email id and address.\n\n4. Select the complaint type, based on the value of your grievance claim.\n\n5. Write a detailed description of the complaint in the provided box. You can write the description in both Hindi and English.\n\n6. Attach any supporting documents related to the complaint. Enter the captcha code displayed on the screen.\n\n7. Click on the \"Submit\" button to file the complaint.\n\n8.After submitting the complaint, you will receive a complaint ID that you can use to track the status of the complaint.\n\n9. You can pay court fees online through UPI or net banking. Do not refresh or press back the page until the payment is completed. In case of failed payment, the case will be listed under the ‘check fail transaction category’ in the case filing menu.\n\n10. Offline payments may be fulfilled through bank demand drafts (DDS) or Indian Postal Orders (IPOS), challan, or NEFT/RTGS.\n\nWithin 48 hours, the case will be acknowledged, and the redress process will begin, which takes one month to complete. Besides, you can also track the messages sent to the brand and consumer.    	', 'E-Daakhil: File Grahak Complaints From anywhere', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'e-daakhil-file-consumer-complaints-from-anywhere', '', '', '2023-08-10 11:25:10', '2023-08-10 11:25:10', '', 0, 'http://localhost/bolograhak/blog/?p=250', 6, 'post', '', 0),
(317, 1, '2023-08-12 11:51:33', '2023-08-12 11:51:33', 'Customer reviews are mainly opinions that customers write about a company\'s products and services for others to read. Many people read these reviews to learn more about businesses and research their products or services before making a purchase. And customers are 63% more likely to trust brands with online reviews compared to brands with no reviews. Actually, it has created a new field in online marketing and communication that bridges the gap between traditional word-of-mouth and a viral form of feedback.\nHere are five important reasons why online customer reviews are important.\n<strong>1. Provide social proof:</strong>\nOnline reviews provide social proof to potential customers. They probably won’t believe everything you have to say about the product or service. However, personal recommendations and word-of-mouth are much more powerful.\n\n<strong>2. online reviews validate expertise:</strong>\nMost consumers trust online reviews by their peers more than the claims made by a company. Consumers are less likely to believe a claim if there isn’t any third-party supporting evidence. Good reviews are a great way to back up your claims.\n\n<strong>3. Influence purchasing decisions:</strong>\nOnline reviews directly influence the buying decisions of your target market. According to one study, having as few as five reviews makes products 270% more likely to sell compared to products with no reviews.\n\n4. Reviews Generate More Reviews:\nThe appearance of several reviews seems to be opinion enough to give new customers the incentive and confidence to submit their own on a particular product or service. So, it encourages other visitors to leave their own feedback.\n\n5. Better understands your customers and improve Customer Service:\nCustomer reviews can tell you things you may not know, including human factors such as staff behaviour. Not everyone complains when they are dissatisfied. But all the reviews left by your customers, helps your company understands overall customer satisfaction and customer service.    	', 'Five top reasons why customer reviews are important', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', '__trashed', '', '', '2023-08-12 11:51:33', '2023-08-12 11:51:33', '', 0, 'http://localhost/bolograhak/blog/?p=316', 1, 'post', '', 0),
